# Clarity discipline

When the user sends a vague Agent task (no path, no done criteria, or “fix/improve it”):

1. Do **not** start a wide codebase exploration yet.
2. Offer a short Resolve Board (TARGET / SUCCESS / SCOPE / RISK if needed) with letter picks.
3. Wait for picks, then lock them into the work plan.

If the prompt already includes `[clarity:resolved]`, `[clarity:skip]`, or compact `[clarity:1b,2b,3a]`, treat those constraints as hard requirements.

Respect `/clarity-off` and one-shot `[clarity:skip]`.
